Introduction

KATSEYE is a six-member global girl group under HYBE Labels and Geffen Records. The group was made in collaboration with HYBE x Geffen Records for the survival show “The Debut: Dream Academy“. The members of KATSEYE are Manon, Sophia, Daniela, Lara, Megan, and Yoonchae.

On June 28, 2024, KATSEYE unveiled their pre-debut song, "Debut". A month later, on July 26, 2024, they released their second pre-debut track, "Touch", which quickly went viral across all platforms, reaching over 14 million monthly listeners on Spotify, generating almost 400 thousand TikTok videos using the sound, and amassing more than 4 million followers across various platforms.

Following the success of their pre-debut releases, KATSEYE dropped their first EP, titled "SIS (Soft Is Strong)", on August 16, 2024. The EP features five tracks, including their pre-debut hits "Debut" and "Touch", whom the popularity allowed the EP to make a remarkable entry on the Billboard 200 Album Charts at #119, marking KATSEYE as the first Global/Western girl group to achieve this feat.
